One thing they mentioned on Lord of Spirits podcast is how all (extremely rare) stories of a fallen angel repenting, or a dead man whose soul is in Hades being saved, etc. always involve a living human's prayer or action. Mortality and material bodies are just insanely powerful.

It's the human repenting *for* them, material bodies are the vehicles through which the process is able to occur. You can't repent after death because you no longer have the body's potentiality. This is why it's also essential to pray for the salvation of dead relatives, friends.

It's not really a main thing, I think it's more of a sidelines thing that you generally try not to talk about too much because it can be counter-productive and you only tell people who despair over dead loved ones about it
